p1: [
  "GATE 0 is necessary but not sufficient. It checks right-question launch, packed-question equality, and title-stub rejection, but it does not require immutable artifact lineage from task_id -> packed prompt -> raw answer -> rendered report -> judge input -> score row. Split-brain scoring can still survive through stale report reads, stale packed prompts, or evaluator/report mismatches. Add manifest hashes and negative canaries for each former drb_72 failure mode before any bake-off score is trusted.",
  "The bake-off currently confounds query-generation mechanism with full-system differences. AgentCPM/WARP, DuMate, WebWeaver, FS-Researcher, Tongyi, etc. include planning, retrieval, memory, writing, and sometimes trained-agent behavior; standalone scores cannot by themselves identify which query-generation front-end POLARIS should secure. Add a controlled mode where each runnable candidate emits normalized query/roadmap artifacts into identical POLARIS retrieval/generation/verification budgets; standalone full-stack scores may screen, but not decide the mechanism.",
  "The screening design is too noisy for decision-grade selection. A 10-15 task subset with no repeated/paired design, confidence intervals, retrieval snapshot/cache, or minimum effect threshold can select the wrong top 1-2 under GLM-5.2 and web-retrieval variance. Require a locked stratified task list, fixed tool/retrieval budget, paired per-task scoring, bootstrap/significance or non-overlap criteria, and reruns for finalists.",
  "Faithfulness non-regression is directionally right but not operational. 'Watched' and 'regresses => loses' need quantitative gates: baseline floor, allowed tolerance, per-metric noninferiority thresholds for DEER/DeepTRACE/DeepScholar sentence-verifiability, and a policy for citation precision / unsupported-claim severity. Without that, coverage gains can be accepted or rejected arbitrarily.",
  "The frontier mandate is not yet executable. The plan names the required seven, but lacks a build-start primary-source rescan with inclusion/exclusion logging, exact arXiv/repo/version pins, and runnability evidence. Primary-source scan indicates additional 2025-2026 candidates needing include/exclude rationale, including PokeeResearch-7B arXiv 2510.15862 with repo, DeepResearch-R1/DeepResearch-9K arXiv 2603.01152 with repo, and DOLORES arXiv 2605.11388; I could not verify ScaffoldAgent arXiv 2606.20122 from public search results.",
  "GLM-5.2 adaptation rules are underspecified. Some candidates are framework-level, some are trained agents/models, and some may depend on native tool stacks. The plan must define whether candidates run as native systems, GLM-5.2-backed scaffolds, or excluded as unrunnable; otherwise the result mixes mechanism quality, model training, tool availability, and adapter effort."
]
